#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:3.1"
msgid "1. Paribbājakakathā"
msgstr "Talk on Wanderers"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.1"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:4.1"
msgid "<span class=\"evam\">Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​</span>"
msgstr "<span class=”evam”>So I have heard.</span>"

msgctxt "dn1:4.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā antarā ca rājagahaṃ antarā ca nāḷandaṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi "
"bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was travelling along the road between Rājagaha and "
"Nālanda together with a large Saṅgha of around five hundred mendicants."

msgctxt "dn1:4.3"
msgid ""
"Suppiyopi kho paribbājako antarā ca rājagahaṃ antarā ca nāḷandaṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipanno hoti saddhiṃ antevāsinā brahmadattena māṇavena."
msgstr ""
"And the wanderer Suppiya was also travelling along the same road together "
"with his pupil, the brahmin student Brahmadatta."

msgctxt "dn1:4.4"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
"dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;"
msgstr ""
"Meanwhile, Suppiya criticized the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in "
"many ways,"

msgctxt "dn1:4.5"
msgid ""
"suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena "
"buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr "but his pupil Brahmadatta praised them in many ways."

#. VAR: anubandhā → anubaddhā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:4.6"
msgid ""
"Itiha te ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā bhagavantaṃ "
"piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā honti bhikkhusaṃghañca."
msgstr ""
"In this way both teacher and pupil, while directly contradicting each other, "
"followed behind the Buddha and the Saṅgha of mendicants."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.2"></a>
#. VAR: upagacchi → upagañchi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ rājāgārake ekarattivāsaṃ upagacchi saddhiṃ "
"bhikkhusaṃghena."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha took up residence for the night in the royal rest-house in "
"Ambalaṭṭhikā together with the Saṅgha of mendicants."

msgctxt "dn1:5.2"
msgid ""
"Suppiyopi kho paribbājako ambalaṭṭhikāyaṃ rājāgārake ekarattivāsaṃ upagacchi "
"antevāsinā brahmadattena māṇavena."
msgstr "And Suppiya and Brahmadatta did likewise."

msgctxt "dn1:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tatrapi sudaṃ suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
"dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;"
msgstr ""
"There too, Suppiya criticized the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in "
"many ways,"

msgctxt "dn1:5.4"
msgid ""
"suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena "
"buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṃghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr "but his pupil Brahmadatta praised them in many ways."

msgctxt "dn1:5.5"
msgid "Itiha te ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"In this way both teacher and pupil kept directly contradicting each other."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhitānaṃ "
"maṇḍalamāḷe sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayaṃ saṅkhiyadhammo udapādi:"
msgstr ""
"Then several mendicants rose at the crack of dawn and sat together in the "
"pavilion. The topic of evaluation came up:"

msgctxt "dn1:6.2"
msgid ""
"“acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā "
"passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sattānaṃ nānādhimuttikatā suppaṭividitā."
msgstr ""
"“It’s incredible, reverends, it’s amazing how the diverse beliefs of "
"sentient beings have been clearly comprehended by the Blessed One, who knows "
"and sees, the Perfect One, the fully awakened Buddha."

msgctxt "dn1:6.3"
msgid ""
"Ayañhi suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
"dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;"
msgstr ""
"For this Suppiya criticizes the Buddha, the teaching, and the Saṅgha in many "
"ways,"

msgctxt "dn1:6.4"
msgid ""
"suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena "
"buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr "while his pupil Brahmadatta praises them in many ways."

msgctxt "dn1:6.5"
msgid ""
"Itihame ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā bhagavantaṃ "
"piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā honti bhikkhusaṅghañcā”ti."
msgstr ""
"In this way both teacher and pupil, while directly contradicting each other, "
"follow behind the Buddha and the Saṅgha of mendicants.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ imaṃ saṅkhiyadhammaṃ viditvā yena "
"maṇḍalamāḷo tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha found out about this discussion on evaluation among the "
"mendicants, he went to the pavilion,"

msgctxt "dn1:7.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat on the seat spread out"

msgctxt "dn1:7.3"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants: "

msgctxt "dn1:7.4"
msgid ""
"“kāya nuttha, bhikkhave, etarahi kathāya sannisinnā sannipatitā, kā ca pana "
"vo antarākathā vippakatā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, what were you sitting talking about just now? What conversation "
"was left unfinished?” "

msgctxt "dn1:7.5"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, te bhikkhū bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "The mendicants told him what had happened, adding:"

msgctxt "dn1:7.6"
msgid ""
"“idha, bhante, amhākaṃ rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhitānaṃ maṇḍalamāḷe "
"sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ ayaṃ saṅkhiyadhammo udapādi:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:7.7"
msgid ""
"‘acchariyaṃ, āvuso, abbhutaṃ, āvuso, yāvañcidaṃ tena bhagavatā jānatā "
"passatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena sattānaṃ nānādhimuttikatā suppaṭividitā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:7.8"
msgid ""
"Ayañhi suppiyo paribbājako anekapariyāyena buddhassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
"dhammassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:7.9"
msgid ""
"suppiyassa pana paribbājakassa antevāsī brahmadatto māṇavo anekapariyāyena "
"buddhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, dhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, saṅghassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:7.10"
msgid ""
"Itihame ubho ācariyantevāsī aññamaññassa ujuvipaccanīkavādā bhagavantaṃ "
"piṭṭhito piṭṭhito anubandhā honti bhikkhusaṅghañcā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:7.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho no, bhante, antarākathā vippakatā, atha bhagavā anuppatto”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This was our conversation that was unfinished when the Buddha arrived.”"

# In line with the former reading of "judgmental", I think this passage is more gently critical of the monks than implied in previous translations. The phrasing here is somewhat unusual and specific, and is more active than just "giving way": they "should not do" what creates bitterness (i.e. sit around judging others). Cp MN 22, where the same phrases are used. In the Buddha's case, it has the neutral hoti, while for the mendicants it uses karaniya, as here. 
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.3"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ "
"bhāseyyuṃ, saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi na āghāto na "
"appaccayo na cetaso anabhiraddhi karaṇīyā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, if others criticize me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, don’t make "
"yourselves resentful, bitter, and emotionally exasperated."

msgctxt "dn1:8.2"
msgid ""
"Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, "
"saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra ce tumhe assatha kupitā vā anattamanā "
"vā, tumhaṃ yevassa tena antarāyo."
msgstr "You’ll only get angry and upset, and that would be an obstacle for you."

msgctxt "dn1:8.3"
msgid ""
"Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, "
"saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra ce tumhe assatha kupitā vā anattamanā "
"vā, api nu tumhe paresaṃ subhāsitaṃ dubbhāsitaṃ ājāneyyāthā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"If others were to criticize me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, and you got "
"angry and upset, would you be able to understand whether they spoke well or "
"poorly?”"

msgctxt "dn1:8.4"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā avaṇṇaṃ "
"bhāseyyuṃ, saṅghassa vā avaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi abhūtaṃ abhūtato "
"nibbeṭhetabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“If others criticize me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, you should explain "
"that what is untrue is in fact untrue:"

msgctxt "dn1:9.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipetaṃ abhūtaṃ, itipetaṃ atacchaṃ, natthi cetaṃ amhesu, na ca panetaṃ "
"amhesu saṃvijjatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This why that’s untrue, this is why that’s false. There’s no such thing in "
"us, it’s not found among us.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a>
#. VAR: uppilāvitattaṃ → ubbilāvitattaṃ (bj, s1-3) | ubbillā­vitat­taṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:10.1"
msgid ""
"Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, "
"saṃghassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi na ānando na somanassaṃ na "
"cetaso uppilāvitattaṃ karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If others praise me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, don’t make yourselves "
"thrilled, elated, and emotionally excited."

#. VAR: uppilāvitā → ubbilāvino (bj) | ubbilāvitattā (s1-3) | ubbillāvitā
#. (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:10.2"
msgid ""
"Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, "
"saṃghassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra ce tumhe assatha ānandino sumanā "
"uppilāvitā tumhaṃ yevassa tena antarāyo."
msgstr ""
"You’ll only get thrilled, elated, and emotionally excited, and that would be "
"an obstacle for you."

msgctxt "dn1:10.3"
msgid ""
"Mamaṃ vā, bhikkhave, pare vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, dhammassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, "
"saṃghassa vā vaṇṇaṃ bhāseyyuṃ, tatra tumhehi bhūtaṃ bhūtato paṭijānitabbaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"If others criticize me, the teaching, or the Saṅgha, you should acknowledge "
"that what is true is in fact true:"

msgctxt "dn1:10.4"
msgid ""
"‘itipetaṃ bhūtaṃ, itipetaṃ tacchaṃ, atthi cetaṃ amhesu, saṃvijjati ca "
"panetaṃ amhesū’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This why that’s true, this is why that’s correct. There is such a thing in "
"us, it is found among us.’"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:11.1"
msgid "2. Sīla"
msgstr "Ethics"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:12.1"
msgid "2.1. Cūḷasīla"
msgstr "The Shorter Section on Ethics"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:13.1"
msgid ""
"Appamattakaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, oramattakaṃ sīlamattakaṃ, yena "
"puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr ""
"When an ordinary person speaks praise of the Realized One, they speak only "
"of trivial, insignificant details of mere ethics."

msgctxt "dn1:13.2"
msgid ""
"Katamañca taṃ, bhikkhave, appamattakaṃ oramattakaṃ sīlamattakaṃ, yena "
"puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya?"
msgstr ""
"And what are the trivial, insignificant details of mere ethics that an "
"ordinary person speaks of?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.4"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:14.1"
msgid ""
"‘Pāṇātipātaṃ pahāya pāṇātipātā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo nihitadaṇḍo, "
"nihitasattho, lajjī, dayāpanno, sabbapāṇabhūtahitānukampī viharatī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has given up killing living creatures. He has renounced "
"violence and harming. He’s scrupulous and kind, living full of compassion "
"for all creatures.’"

msgctxt "dn1:14.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:15.1"
msgid ""
"‘Adinnādānaṃ pahāya adinnādānā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo dinnādāyī "
"dinnapāṭikaṅkhī, athenena sucibhūtena attanā viharatī’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has given up stealing. He takes only what’s given, and "
"expects only what’s given. He keeps himself pure by not thieving.’"

msgctxt "dn1:15.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a>
#. VAR: ārācārī → anācārī (mr)
#. VAR: virato → paṭivirato (katthaci)
msgctxt "dn1:16.1"
msgid ""
"‘Abrahmacariyaṃ pahāya brahmacārī samaṇo gotamo ārācārī virato methunā "
"gāmadhammā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has given up unchastity. He is celibate, set apart, "
"avoiding the common practice of sex.’"

msgctxt "dn1:16.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a>
#. VAR: theto → ṭheto (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "dn1:17.1"
msgid ""
"‘Musāvādaṃ pahāya musāvādā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo saccavādī saccasandho "
"theto paccayiko avisaṃvādako lokassā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has given up lying. He speaks the truth and sticks to "
"the truth. He’s honest and trustworthy, and doesn’t trick the world with his "
"words.’"

msgctxt "dn1:17.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:18.1"
msgid ""
"‘Pisuṇaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pisuṇāya vācāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo, ito sutvā na "
"amutra akkhātā imesaṃ bhedāya, amutra vā sutvā na imesaṃ akkhātā amūsaṃ "
"bhedāya."
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has given up divisive speech. He doesn’t repeat in one "
"place what he heard in another so as to divide people against each other."

msgctxt "dn1:18.2"
msgid ""
"Iti bhinnānaṃ vā sandhātā, sahitānaṃ vā anuppadātā samaggārāmo samaggarato "
"samagganandī samaggakaraṇiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"Instead, he reconciles those who are divided, supporting unity, delighting "
"in harmony, loving harmony, speaking words that promote harmony.’"

msgctxt "dn1:18.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:19.1"
msgid ""
"‘Pharusaṃ vācaṃ pahāya pharusāya vācāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo, yā sā vācā "
"nelā kaṇṇasukhā pemanīyā hadayaṅgamā porī bahujanakantā bahujanamanāpā "
"tathārūpiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has given up harsh speech. He speaks in a way that’s "
"mellow, pleasing to the ear, lovely, going to the heart, polite, likable and "
"agreeable to many people.’"

msgctxt "dn1:19.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.5"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:20.1"
msgid ""
"‘Samphappalāpaṃ pahāya samphappalāpā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo kālavādī "
"bhūtavādī atthavādī dhammavādī vinayavādī, nidhānavatiṃ vācaṃ bhāsitā kālena "
"sāpadesaṃ pariyantavatiṃ atthasaṃhitan’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has given up idle chatter. His words are timely, true, "
"and meaningful, in line with the teaching and training. He says things at "
"the right time which are valuable, reasonable, succinct, and beneficial.’"

msgctxt "dn1:20.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:21.1"
msgid "‘Bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama refrains from injuring plants and seeds.’"

msgctxt "dn1:21.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:21.3"
msgid "pe …."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a>
#. VAR: virato → vikālabhojanā paṭivirato (pts1) | paṭivirato (katthaci)
msgctxt "dn1:22.1"
msgid "‘Ekabhattiko samaṇo gotamo rattūparato virato vikālabhojanā …."
msgstr ""
"‘He eats in one part of the day, abstaining from eating at night and food at "
"the wrong time.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:23.1"
msgid "Naccagītavāditavisūkadassanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "‘He refrains from dancing, singing, music, and seeing shows.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:24.1"
msgid ""
"Mālāgandhavilepanadhāraṇamaṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr ""
"‘He refrains from beautifying and adorning himself with garlands, perfumes, "
"and makeup.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:25.1"
msgid "Uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "‘He refrains from high and luxurious beds.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:26.1"
msgid "Jātarūparajatapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "‘He refrains from receiving gold and money,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:27.1"
msgid "Āmakadhaññapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "raw grains,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:28.1"
msgid "Āmakamaṃsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "raw meat,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:29.1"
msgid "Itthikumārikapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "women and girls,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:30.1"
msgid "Dāsidāsapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "male and female bondservants,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:31.1"
msgid "Ajeḷakapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "goats and sheep,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:32.1"
msgid "Kukkuṭasūkarapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "chickens and pigs,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:33.1"
msgid "Hatthigavassavaḷavapaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "elephants, cows, horses, and mares,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:34.1"
msgid "Khettavatthupaṭiggahaṇā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "and fields and land.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:35.1"
msgid "Dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "‘He refrains from running errands and messages;"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:36.1"
msgid "Kayavikkayā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "buying and selling;"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:37.1"
msgid "Tulākūṭakaṃsakūṭamānakūṭā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "falsifying weights, metals, or measures;"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="33"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:38.1"
msgid "Ukkoṭanavañcananikatisāciyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo …."
msgstr "bribery, fraud, cheating, and duplicity;"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="34"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:39.1"
msgid ""
"Chedanavadhabandhanaviparāmosaālopasahasākārā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "mutilation, murder, abduction, banditry, plunder, and violence.’"

msgctxt "dn1:39.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:40.1"
msgid "Cūḷasīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The shorter section on ethics is finished."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:41.1"
msgid "2.2. Majjhimasīla"
msgstr "The Middle Section on Ethics"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a>
#. VAR: seyyathidaṃ → seyyathīdaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:42.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in injuring plants and seeds."

# See my note on SN 22.54
#. VAR: pañcamaṃ → pañcamaṃ iti vā (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:42.2"
msgid "mūlabījaṃ khandhabījaṃ phaḷubījaṃ aggabījaṃ bījabījameva pañcamaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"These include plants propagated from roots, stems, cuttings, or joints; and "
"those from regular seeds as the fifth."

msgctxt "dn1:42.3"
msgid "iti evarūpā bījagāmabhūtagāmasamārambhā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr "The ascetic Gotama refrains from such injury to plants and seeds.’"

msgctxt "dn1:42.4"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.6"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:43.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ sannidhikāraparibhogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in storing up goods for their own enjoyment."

msgctxt "dn1:43.2"
msgid ""
"annasannidhiṃ pānasannidhiṃ vatthasannidhiṃ yānasannidhiṃ sayanasannidhiṃ "
"gandhasannidhiṃ āmisasannidhiṃ iti vā iti evarūpā sannidhikāraparibhogā "
"paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as food, drink, clothes, vehicles, bedding, "
"fragrance, and material possessions. The ascetic Gotama refrains from "
"storing up such goods.’"

msgctxt "dn1:43.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:44.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ visūkadassanaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in seeing shows."

# uyyodhika in the suttas is only used here and at AN 10.30, where is not a sham. And the definition at Pc 50 says Uyyodhikaṃ nāma yattha sampahāro dissati "where strife is seen". 
#. VAR: meṇḍayuddhaṃ → meṇḍakayuddhaṃ (pts1)
#. VAR: sobhanakaṃ → sobhanagarakaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: mahiṃsayuddhaṃ → mahisayuddhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: kumbhathūṇaṃ → kumbhathūnaṃ (bj, s1-3, mr)
#. VAR: dhovanaṃ → dhopanaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:44.2"
msgid ""
"naccaṃ gītaṃ vāditaṃ pekkhaṃ akkhānaṃ pāṇissaraṃ vetāḷaṃ kumbhathūṇaṃ "
"sobhanakaṃ caṇḍālaṃ vaṃsaṃ dhovanaṃ hatthiyuddhaṃ assayuddhaṃ mahiṃsayuddhaṃ "
"usabhayuddhaṃ ajayuddhaṃ meṇḍayuddhaṃ kukkuṭayuddhaṃ vaṭṭakayuddhaṃ "
"daṇḍayuddhaṃ muṭṭhiyuddhaṃ nibbuddhaṃ uyyodhikaṃ balaggaṃ senābyūhaṃ "
"anīkadassanaṃ iti vā iti evarūpā visūkadassanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as dancing, singing, music, performances, and "
"story telling; clapping, gongs, and kettle-drums; art exhibitions and "
"acrobatic displays; battles of elephants, horses, buffaloes, bulls, goats, "
"rams, chickens and quails; staff-fights, boxing, and wrestling; combat, roll "
"calls of the armed forces, battle-formations, and regimental reviews. The "
"ascetic Gotama refrains from such shows.’"

msgctxt "dn1:44.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

# While gambling isn't mentioned explicitly here, jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyoga is treated in DN 31 exclusively as gambling, so it seems that is implied.
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.7"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:45.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in gambling that causes negligence."

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/some-brief-notes-on-games/5329
#. VAR: ciṅgulikaṃ → ciṅgulakaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "dn1:45.2"
msgid ""
"aṭṭhapadaṃ dasapadaṃ ākāsaṃ parihārapathaṃ santikaṃ khalikaṃ ghaṭikaṃ "
"salākahatthaṃ akkhaṃ paṅgacīraṃ vaṅkakaṃ mokkhacikaṃ ciṅgulikaṃ pattāḷhakaṃ "
"rathakaṃ dhanukaṃ akkharikaṃ manesikaṃ yathāvajjaṃ iti vā iti evarūpā "
"jūtappamādaṭṭhānānuyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as checkers, draughts, checkers in the air, "
"hopscotch, spillikins, board-games, tip-cat, drawing straws, dice, leaf-"
"flutes, toy ploughs, somersaults, pinwheels, toy measures, toy carts, toy "
"bows, guessing words from syllables, and guessing another’s thoughts. The "
"ascetic Gotama refrains from such gambling.’"

msgctxt "dn1:45.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:46.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ uccāsayanamahāsayanaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still make use of high and luxurious bedding."

#. VAR: hatthattharaṃ assattharaṃ rathattharaṃ → hatthat­thara­ṇaṃ
#. assattharaṇaṃ rathattharaṇaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:46.2"
msgid ""
"āsandiṃ pallaṅkaṃ gonakaṃ cittakaṃ paṭikaṃ paṭalikaṃ tūlikaṃ vikatikaṃ "
"uddalomiṃ ekantalomiṃ kaṭṭissaṃ koseyyaṃ kuttakaṃ hatthattharaṃ assattharaṃ "
"rathattharaṃ ajinappaveṇiṃ kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇaṃ sauttaracchadaṃ "
"ubhatolohitakūpadhānaṃ iti vā iti evarūpā uccāsayanamahāsayanā paṭivirato "
"samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes such things as sofas, couches, woolen covers—shag-piled, "
"colorful, white, embroidered with flowers, quilted, embroidered with "
"animals, double- or single-fringed—and silk covers studded with gems, as "
"well as silken sheets, woven carpets, rugs for elephants, horses, or "
"chariots, antelope hide rugs, and spreads of fine deer hide, with a canopy "
"above and red cushions at both ends. The ascetic Gotama refrains from such "
"bedding.’"

msgctxt "dn1:46.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="40"></a>
#. VAR: daṇḍaṃ → daṇḍakaṃ (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: nāḷikaṃ → nālikaṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: asiṃ → asiṃ khaggaṃ (s1-3, km) | khaggaṃ (pts1)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn1:47.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ maṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ–  "
"ucchādanaṃ parimaddanaṃ nhāpanaṃ sambāhanaṃ ādāsaṃ añjanaṃ "
"mālāgandhavilepanaṃ mukhacuṇṇaṃ mukhalepanaṃ hatthabandhaṃ sikhābandhaṃ "
"daṇḍaṃ nāḷikaṃ asiṃ chattaṃ citrupāhanaṃ uṇhīsaṃ maṇiṃ vālabījaniṃ odātāni "
"vatthāni dīghadasāni iti vā iti evarūpā maṇḍanavibhūsanaṭṭhānānuyogā "
"paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in beautifying and adorning themselves with garlands, "
"fragrance, and makeup. This includes such things as applying beauty products "
"by anointing, massaging, bathing, and rubbing; mirrors, ointments, garlands, "
"fragrances, and makeup; face-powder, foundation, bracelets, head-bands, "
"fancy walking-sticks or containers, rapiers, parasols, fancy sandals, "
"turbans, jewelry, choweries, and long-fringed white robes. The ascetic "
"Gotama refrains from such beautification and adornment.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:47.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.8"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:48.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in unworthy talk."

#. VAR: itthikathaṃ → itthīkathaṃ (bj) | itthikathaṃ purisakathaṃ (s1, km, mr)
#. | itthīkathaṃ purisakathaṃ (s2, s3)
msgctxt "dn1:48.2"
msgid ""
"rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ "
"annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ "
"ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ "
"itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ "
"nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā iti "
"evarūpāya tiracchānakathāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes such topics as talk about kings, bandits, and ministers; talk "
"about armies, threats, and wars; talk about food, drink, clothes, and beds; "
"talk about garlands and fragrances; talk about family, vehicles, villages, "
"towns, cities, and countries; talk about women and heroes; street talk and "
"well talk; talk about the departed; motley talk; tales of land and sea; and "
"talk about being reborn in this or that state of existence. The ascetic "
"Gotama refrains from such unworthy talk."

msgctxt "dn1:48.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:49.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ viggāhikakathaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in arguments."

#. VAR: adhiciṇṇaṃ → āciṇṇaṃ (bj) | aviciṇṇaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:49.2"
msgid ""
"na tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāsi, ahaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānāmi, kiṃ "
"tvaṃ imaṃ dhammavinayaṃ ājānissasi, micchā paṭipanno tvamasi, ahamasmi sammā "
"paṭipanno, sahitaṃ me, asahitaṃ te, purevacanīyaṃ pacchā avaca, "
"pacchāvacanīyaṃ pure avaca, adhiciṇṇaṃ te viparāvattaṃ, āropito te vādo, "
"niggahito tvamasi, cara vādappamokkhāya, nibbeṭhehi vā sace pahosīti iti vā "
"iti evarūpāya viggāhikakathāya paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"They say such things as: “You don’t understand this teaching and training. I "
"understand this teaching and training. What, you understand this teaching "
"and training? You’re practicing wrong. I’m practicing right. I stay on "
"topic, you don’t. You said last what you should have said first. You said "
"first what you should have said last. What you’ve thought so much about has "
"been disproved. Your doctrine is refuted. Go on, save your doctrine! You’re "
"trapped; get yourself out of this—if you can!” The ascetic Gotama refrains "
"from such argumentative talk."

msgctxt "dn1:49.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:50.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpaṃ dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogaṃ anuyuttā viharanti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in running errands and messages."

msgctxt "dn1:50.2"
msgid ""
"raññaṃ, rājamahāmattānaṃ, khattiyānaṃ, brāhmaṇānaṃ, gahapatikānaṃ, kumārānaṃ "
"“idha gaccha, amutrāgaccha, idaṃ hara, amutra idaṃ āharā”ti iti vā iti "
"evarūpā dūteyyapahiṇagamanānuyogā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes running errands for rulers, ministers, aristocrats, brahmins, "
"householders, or princes who say: “Go here, go there. Take this, bring that "
"from there.” The ascetic Gotama refrains from such errands."

msgctxt "dn1:50.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a>
#. VAR: iti → iti (bj, mr)
#. VAR: lābhena lābhaṃ nijigīsitāro ca → lābhena ca lābhaṃ nijigiṃsitāro (bj,
#. s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:51.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"kuhakā ca honti, lapakā ca nemittikā ca nippesikā ca, lābhena lābhaṃ "
"nijigīsitāro ca iti evarūpā kuhanalapanā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still engage in deception, flattery, hinting, and belittling, and "
"using material possessions to pursue other material possessions. The ascetic "
"Gotama refrains from such deception and flattery.’"

msgctxt "dn1:51.2"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:52.1"
msgid "Majjhimasīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The middle section on ethics is finished."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:53.1"
msgid "2.3. Mahāsīla"
msgstr "The Large Section on Ethics"

# Translations of tiracchana in such contexts (debased, low, etc.) are often harsher than the old explanations. In Bhi pc 49-50, we have Tiracchā­na­vijjā nāma yaṃ kiñci bāhirakaṃ anat­tha­saṃhi­taṃ, while the commentary says Tiracchānavijjā nāma aniyyānikattā saggamokkhamaggānaṃ tiracchānabhūtā. 
#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.9"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:54.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

#. VAR: khattavijjā → khettavijjā (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn1:54.2"
msgid ""
"aṅgaṃ nimittaṃ uppātaṃ supinaṃ lakkhaṇaṃ mūsikacchinnaṃ aggihomaṃ dabbihomaṃ "
"thusahomaṃ kaṇahomaṃ taṇḍulahomaṃ sappihomaṃ telahomaṃ mukhahomaṃ "
"lohitahomaṃ aṅgavijjā vatthuvijjā khattavijjā sivavijjā bhūtavijjā "
"bhūrivijjā ahivijjā visavijjā vicchikavijjā mūsikavijjā sakuṇavijjā "
"vāyasavijjā pakkajjhānaṃ saraparittāṇaṃ migacakkaṃ iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes such fields as limb-reading, omenology, divining celestial "
"portents, interpreting dreams, divining bodily marks, divining holes in "
"cloth gnawed by mice, fire offerings, ladle offerings, offerings of husks, "
"rice powder, rice, ghee, or oil; offerings from the mouth, blood sacrifices, "
"palmistry; geomancy for building sites, fields, and cemeteries; exorcisms, "
"earth magic, snake charming, poisons; the crafts of the scorpion, the rat, "
"the bird, and the crow; prophesying life span, chanting for protection, and "
"animal cries. The ascetic Gotama refrains from such unworthy branches of "
"knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’"

msgctxt "dn1:54.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="46"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:55.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn1:55.2"
msgid ""
"maṇilakkhaṇaṃ vatthalakkhaṇaṃ daṇḍalakkhaṇaṃ satthalakkhaṇaṃ asilakkhaṇaṃ "
"usulakkhaṇaṃ dhanulakkhaṇaṃ āvudhalakkhaṇaṃ itthilakkhaṇaṃ purisalakkhaṇaṃ "
"kumāralakkhaṇaṃ kumārilakkhaṇaṃ dāsalakkhaṇaṃ dāsilakkhaṇaṃ hatthilakkhaṇaṃ "
"assalakkhaṇaṃ mahiṃsalakkhaṇaṃ usabhalakkhaṇaṃ golakkhaṇaṃ ajalakkhaṇaṃ "
"meṇḍalakkhaṇaṃ kukkuṭalakkhaṇaṃ vaṭṭakalakkhaṇaṃ godhālakkhaṇaṃ "
"kaṇṇikālakkhaṇaṃ kacchapalakkhaṇaṃ migalakkhaṇaṃ iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes reading the marks of gems, cloth, clubs, swords, spears, "
"arrows, weapons, women, men, boys, girls, male and female bondservants, "
"elephants, horses, buffaloes, bulls, cows, goats, rams, chickens, quails, "
"monitor lizards, rabbits, tortoises, or deer. The ascetic Gotama refrains "
"from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’"

msgctxt "dn1:55.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.10"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:56.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn1:56.2"
msgid ""
"raññaṃ niyyānaṃ bhavissati, raññaṃ aniyyānaṃ bhavissati, abbhantarānaṃ "
"raññaṃ upayānaṃ bhavissati, bāhirānaṃ raññaṃ apayānaṃ bhavissati, bāhirānaṃ "
"raññaṃ upayānaṃ bhavissati, abbhantarānaṃ raññaṃ apayānaṃ bhavissati, "
"abbhantarānaṃ raññaṃ jayo bhavissati, bāhirānaṃ raññaṃ parājayo bhavissati, "
"bāhirānaṃ raññaṃ jayo bhavissati, abbhantarānaṃ raññaṃ parājayo bhavissati, "
"iti imassa jayo bhavissati, imassa parājayo bhavissati iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes making predictions that the king will march forth or march "
"back; or that our king will attack and the enemy king will retreat, or vice "
"versa; or that our king will triumph and the enemy king will be defeated, or "
"vice versa; and so there will be victory for one and defeat for the other. "
"The ascetic Gotama refrains from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such "
"wrong livelihood.’"

msgctxt "dn1:56.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.11"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:57.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

#. VAR: sūriyaggāho → suriyaggāho (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: devadudrabhi → devadundubhi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:57.2"
msgid ""
"candaggāho bhavissati, sūriyaggāho bhavissati, nakkhattaggāho bhavissati, "
"candimasūriyānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, candimasūriyānaṃ uppathagamanaṃ "
"bhavissati, nakkhattānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, nakkhattānaṃ "
"uppathagamanaṃ bhavissati, ukkāpāto bhavissati, disāḍāho bhavissati, "
"bhūmicālo bhavissati, devadudrabhi bhavissati, candimasūriyanakkhattānaṃ "
"uggamanaṃ ogamanaṃ saṃkilesaṃ vodānaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipāko candaggāho "
"bhavissati, evaṃvipāko sūriyaggāho bhavissati, evaṃvipāko nakkhattaggāho "
"bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, "
"evaṃvipākaṃ candimasūriyānaṃ uppathagamanaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ "
"nakkhattānaṃ pathagamanaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ nakkhattānaṃ "
"uppathagamanaṃ bhavissati, evaṃvipāko ukkāpāto bhavissati, evaṃvipāko "
"disāḍāho bhavissati, evaṃvipāko bhūmicālo bhavissati, evaṃvipāko "
"devadudrabhi bhavissati, evaṃvipākaṃ candimasūriyanakkhattānaṃ uggamanaṃ "
"ogamanaṃ saṃkilesaṃ vodānaṃ bhavissati iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes making predictions that there will be an eclipse of the moon, "
"or sun, or stars; that the sun, moon, and stars will be in conjunction or in "
"opposition; that there will be a meteor shower, a fiery sky, an earthquake, "
"thunder; that there will be a rising, a setting, a darkening, a brightening "
"of the moon, sun, and stars. And it also includes making predictions about "
"the results of all such phenomena. The ascetic Gotama refrains from such "
"unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’"

msgctxt "dn1:57.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:58.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn1:58.2"
msgid ""
"suvuṭṭhikā bhavissati, dubbuṭṭhikā bhavissati, subhikkhaṃ bhavissati, "
"dubbhikkhaṃ bhavissati, khemaṃ bhavissati, bhayaṃ bhavissati, rogo "
"bhavissati, ārogyaṃ bhavissati, muddā, gaṇanā, saṅkhānaṃ, kāveyyaṃ, "
"lokāyataṃ iti vā iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato "
"samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes predicting whether there will be plenty of rain or drought; "
"plenty to eat or famine; an abundant harvest or a bad harvest; security or "
"peril; sickness or health. It also includes such occupations as computing, "
"accounting, calculating, poetry, and cosmology. The ascetic Gotama refrains "
"from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’"

msgctxt "dn1:58.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:59.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

# Omitting hanujappana as it is absent from comm.
msgctxt "dn1:59.2"
msgid ""
"āvāhanaṃ vivāhanaṃ saṃvaraṇaṃ vivaraṇaṃ saṃkiraṇaṃ vikiraṇaṃ subhagakaraṇaṃ "
"dubbhagakaraṇaṃ viruddhagabbhakaraṇaṃ jivhānibandhanaṃ hanusaṃhananaṃ "
"hatthābhijappanaṃ hanujappanaṃ kaṇṇajappanaṃ ādāsapañhaṃ kumārikapañhaṃ "
"devapañhaṃ ādiccupaṭṭhānaṃ mahatupaṭṭhānaṃ abbhujjalanaṃ sirivhāyanaṃ iti vā "
"iti evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes making arrangements for giving and taking in marriage; for "
"engagement and divorce; and for scattering rice inwards or outwards at the "
"wedding ceremony. It also includes casting spells for good or bad luck, "
"curses to prevent conception, bind the tongue, or lock the jaws; charms for "
"the hands and ears; questioning a mirror, a girl, or a god as an oracle; "
"worshiping the sun, worshiping the Great One, breathing fire, and invoking "
"Siri, the goddess of luck. The ascetic Gotama refrains from such unworthy "
"branches of knowledge, such wrong livelihood.’"

msgctxt "dn1:59.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.12"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:60.1"
msgid ""
"‘Yathā vā paneke bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā saddhādeyyāni bhojanāni bhuñjitvā te "
"evarūpāya tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"‘There are some ascetics and brahmins who, while enjoying food given in "
"faith, still earn a living by unworthy branches of knowledge, by wrong "
"livelihood."

msgctxt "dn1:60.2"
msgid ""
"santikammaṃ paṇidhikammaṃ bhūtakammaṃ bhūrikammaṃ vassakammaṃ vossakammaṃ "
"vatthukammaṃ vatthuparikammaṃ ācamanaṃ nhāpanaṃ juhanaṃ vamanaṃ virecanaṃ "
"uddhaṃvirecanaṃ adhovirecanaṃ sīsavirecanaṃ kaṇṇatelaṃ nettatappanaṃ "
"natthukammaṃ añjanaṃ paccañjanaṃ sālākiyaṃ sallakattiyaṃ dārakatikicchā "
"mūlabhesajjānaṃ anuppadānaṃ osadhīnaṃ paṭimokkho iti vā iti evarūpāya "
"tiracchānavijjāya micchājīvā paṭivirato samaṇo gotamo’ti—"
msgstr ""
"This includes rites for propitiation, for fulfilling wishes, for ghosts, for "
"the earth, for rain, for property settlement, and for preparing and "
"consecrating house sites, and those involving rinsing and bathing, and "
"oblations. It also includes administering emetics, purgatives, expectorants "
"and phlegmagogues; administering ear-oils, eye restoratives, nasal medicine, "
"ointments and counter-ointments; surgery with needle and scalpel, treating "
"children, prescribing root medicines, and binding on herbs. The ascetic "
"Gotama refrains from such unworthy branches of knowledge, such wrong "
"livelihood.’"

msgctxt "dn1:60.3"
msgid "iti vā hi, bhikkhave, puthujjano tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr "Such is an ordinary person’s praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:61.1"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, appamattakaṃ oramattakaṃ sīlamattakaṃ, yena puthujjano "
"tathāgatassa vaṇṇaṃ vadamāno vadeyya."
msgstr ""
"These are the trivial, insignificant details of mere ethics that an ordinary "
"person speaks of when they speak praise of the Realized One."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:62.1"
msgid "Mahāsīlaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The longer section on ethics is finished."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:63.1"
msgid "3. Diṭṭhi"
msgstr "Views"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:64.1"
msgid "3.1. Pubbantakappika"
msgstr "Theories About the Past"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:65.1"
msgid ""
"Atthi, bhikkhave, aññeva dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā "
"atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are other principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, "
"sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—"
"which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own "
"insight. Those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of "
"these things."

msgctxt "dn1:65.2"
msgid ""
"Katame ca te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā "
"atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ?"
msgstr "And what are these principles?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.13"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:66.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino, "
"pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi "
"vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past, and assert "
"various hypotheses concerning the past on eighteen grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:66.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha pubbantakappikā "
"pubbantānudiṭṭhino pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni "
"abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the eighteen grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:67.1"
msgid "3.1.1. Sassatavāda"
msgstr "Eternalism"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:68.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā, sassataṃ attānañca lokañca "
"paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who are eternalists, who assert that "
"the self and the cosmos are eternal on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:68.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha sassatavādā sassataṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the four grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.14"></a>
#. VAR: () → (parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe viga­tū­pak­kilese) (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:69.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte () anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ "
"anussarati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and "
"diligent effort, and right focus—experiences a samādhi of the heart of such "
"a kind that they recollect their many kinds of past lives."

msgctxt "dn1:69.2"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "That is:"

msgctxt "dn1:69.3"
msgid ""
"ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo "
"dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi "
"jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekānipi jātisatāni "
"anekānipi jātisahassāni anekānipi jātisatasahassāni:"
msgstr ""
"one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a "
"thousand, a hundred thousand lives; many eons of the cosmos contracting, "
"many eons of the cosmos evolving, many eons of the cosmos contracting and "
"evolving. They remember:"

#. VAR: udapādiṃ → upapādiṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:69.4"
msgid ""
"‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was "
"my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life "
"ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. "

msgctxt "dn1:69.5"
msgid ""
"tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti."
msgstr ""
"There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that "
"was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life "
"ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’"

msgctxt "dn1:69.6"
msgid "Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and "
"details."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:70.1"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "dn1:70.2"
msgid "‘sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito;"
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, "
"standing firm like a pillar."

msgctxt "dn1:70.3"
msgid ""
"te ca sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva "
"sassatisamaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They remain the same for all eternity, while these sentient beings wander "
"and transmigrate and pass away and rearise."

msgctxt "dn1:70.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:70.5"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya "
"sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ cetosamādhiṃ phusāmi, yathāsamāhite citte "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi."
msgstr ""
"Because by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right "
"focus I experience a samādhi of the heart of such a kind that I recollect my "
"many kinds of past lives,"

msgctxt "dn1:70.6"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:70.7"
msgid ""
"ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo "
"dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi "
"jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi anekānipi jātisatāni "
"anekānipi jātisahassāni anekānipi jātisatasahassāni:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:70.8"
msgid ""
"“amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:70.9"
msgid ""
"tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:70.10"
msgid "Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi."
msgstr "with features and details."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:71.1"
msgid "Imināmahaṃ etaṃ jānāmi:"
msgstr "Because of this I know:"

msgctxt "dn1:71.2"
msgid "“yathā sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito;"
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, "
"standing firm like a pillar."

msgctxt "dn1:71.3"
msgid ""
"te ca sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva "
"sassatisaman”’ti."
msgstr ""
"They remain the same for all eternity, while these sentient beings wander "
"and transmigrate and pass away and rearise.’”"

msgctxt "dn1:71.4"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the first ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:71.5"
msgid "(1: 1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.15"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:72.1"
msgid ""
"Dutiye ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha sassatavādā sassataṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti?"
msgstr "And what is the second ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:72.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ "
"anussarati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and "
"diligent effort, and right focus—experiences a samādhi of the heart of such "
"a kind that they recollect their many kinds of past lives."

msgctxt "dn1:72.3"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "That is:"

msgctxt "dn1:72.4"
msgid ""
"ekampi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭaṃ dvepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni tīṇipi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni "
"cattāripi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni pañcapi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni dasapi "
"saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭāni:"
msgstr ""
"one eon of the cosmos contracting and evolving; two, three, four, five, or "
"ten eons of the cosmos contracting and evolving. They remember:"

msgctxt "dn1:72.5"
msgid ""
"‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘There, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that was "
"my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life "
"ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn somewhere else. "

msgctxt "dn1:72.6"
msgid ""
"tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti."
msgstr ""
"There, too, I was named this, my clan was that, I looked like this, and that "
"was my food. This was how I felt pleasure and pain, and that was how my life "
"ended. When I passed away from that place I was reborn here.’"

msgctxt "dn1:72.7"
msgid "Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati."
msgstr ""
"And so they recollect their many kinds of past lives, with features and "
"details. "

