#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:77.1"
msgid "Imināmahaṃ etaṃ jānāmi:"
msgstr "Because of this I know:"

msgctxt "dn1:77.2"
msgid ""
"“yathā sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito, te ca "
"sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva "
"sassatisaman”’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, "
"standing firm like a pillar. They remain the same for all eternity, while "
"these sentient beings wander and transmigrate and pass away and rearise.’”"

msgctxt "dn1:77.3"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the third ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:77.4"
msgid "(3: 3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="65"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:78.1"
msgid ""
"Catutthe ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha sassatavādā sassataṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti?"
msgstr "And what is the fourth ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:78.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā takkī hoti vīmaṃsī, so "
"takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayaṃ paṭibhānaṃ evamāha:"
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin relies on logic and inquiry. They speak of "
"what they have worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, expressing "
"their own perspective:"

msgctxt "dn1:78.3"
msgid "‘sassato attā ca loko ca vañjho kūṭaṭṭho esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhito;"
msgstr ""
"‘The self and the cosmos are eternal, barren, steady as a mountain peak, "
"standing firm like a pillar."

msgctxt "dn1:78.4"
msgid ""
"te ca sattā sandhāvanti saṃsaranti cavanti upapajjanti, atthi tveva "
"sassatisaman’ti."
msgstr ""
"They remain the same for all eternity, while these sentient beings wander "
"and transmigrate and pass away and rearise.’"

msgctxt "dn1:78.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:78.6"
msgid "(4: 4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="66"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:79.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca "
"lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the four grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins assert that "
"the self and the cosmos are eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:79.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca "
"lokañca paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva catūhi vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena;"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who assert that the self and the cosmos are "
"eternal do so on one or other of these four grounds."

# I have my doubts about this phrase: in every other occurrence, ito bahiddha means "outside of the Buddhist community". Still, comm and the Chinese text at T21 agree on this sense.
msgctxt "dn1:79.3"
msgid "natthi ito bahiddhā."
msgstr "Outside of this there is none."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="67"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.17"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:80.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato pajānāti:"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn1:80.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime diṭṭhiṭṭhānā evaṃgahitā evaṃparāmaṭṭhā evaṃgatikā bhavanti "
"evaṃabhisamparāyā’ti, tañca tathāgato pajānāti, tato ca uttaritaraṃ pajānāti;"
msgstr ""
"‘If you hold on to and attach to these grounds for views it leads to such "
"and such a destiny in the next life.’ "

#. VAR: pajānanaṃ → pajānaṃ (?)
msgctxt "dn1:80.3"
msgid ""
"tañca pajānanaṃ na parāmasati, aparāmasato cassa paccattaññeva nibbuti "
"viditā."
msgstr ""
"He understands this, and what goes beyond this. Yet since he does not "
"misapprehend that understanding, he has realized extinguishment within "
"himself."

msgctxt "dn1:80.4"
msgid ""
"Vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca "
"yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto, bhikkhave, tathāgato."
msgstr ""
"Having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback and "
"escape from feelings, the Realized One is freed through not grasping."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="68"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:81.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā "
"atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are the principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, "
"sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—"
"which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own "
"insight. And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak "
"of these things."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:82.1"
msgid "Paṭhamabhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:83.1"
msgid "3.1.2. Ekaccasassatavāda"
msgstr "Partial Eternalism"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="69"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:84.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā "
"ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi "
"vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who are partial eternalists, who assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are partially eternal and partially not eternal "
"on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:84.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha ekaccasassatikā "
"ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca "
"paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the four grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="70"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:85.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo, yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno "
"accayena ayaṃ loko saṃvaṭṭati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, this cosmos "
"contracts."

msgctxt "dn1:85.2"
msgid "Saṃvaṭṭamāne loke yebhuyyena sattā ābhassarasaṃvattanikā honti."
msgstr ""
"As the cosmos contracts, sentient beings are mostly headed for the realm of "
"streaming radiance."

msgctxt "dn1:85.3"
msgid ""
"Te tattha honti manomayā pītibhakkhā sayaṃpabhā antalikkhacarā "
"subhaṭṭhāyino, ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr ""
"There they are mind-made, feeding on rapture, self-luminous, moving through "
"the sky, steadily glorious, and they remain like that for a very long time."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="71"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:86.1"
msgid ""
"Hoti kho so, bhikkhave, samayo, yaṃ kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno "
"accayena ayaṃ loko vivaṭṭati."
msgstr ""
"There comes a time when, after a very long period has passed, this cosmos "
"expands."

msgctxt "dn1:86.2"
msgid "Vivaṭṭamāne loke suññaṃ brahmavimānaṃ pātubhavati."
msgstr "As it expands an empty mansion of Brahmā appears."

msgctxt "dn1:86.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro satto āyukkhayā vā puññakkhayā vā ābhassarakāyā cavitvā "
"suññaṃ brahmavimānaṃ upapajjati."
msgstr ""
"Then a certain sentient being—due to the running out of their life-span or "
"merit—passes away from that group of radiant deities and is reborn in that "
"empty mansion of Brahmā."

msgctxt "dn1:86.4"
msgid ""
"So tattha hoti manomayo pītibhakkho sayampabho antalikkhacaro subhaṭṭhāyī, "
"ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ tiṭṭhati."
msgstr ""
"There they are mind-made, feeding on rapture, self-luminous, moving through "
"the sky, steadily glorious, and they remain like that for a very long time."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="72"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.18"></a>
#. VAR: uppajjati → upapajjati (s1-3, c1)
msgctxt "dn1:87.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa tattha ekakassa dīgharattaṃ nivusitattā anabhirati paritassanā "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"But after staying there all alone for a long time, they become dissatisfied "
"and anxious:"

msgctxt "dn1:87.2"
msgid "‘aho vata aññepi sattā itthattaṃ āgaccheyyun’ti."
msgstr "‘Oh, if only another being would come to this state of existence.’"

msgctxt "dn1:87.3"
msgid ""
"Atha aññepi sattā āyukkhayā vā puññakkhayā vā ābhassarakāyā cavitvā "
"brahmavimānaṃ upapajjanti tassa sattassa sahabyataṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then other sentient beings—due to the running out of their life-span or "
"merit—pass away from that group of radiant deities and are reborn in that "
"empty mansion of Brahmā in company with that being."

msgctxt "dn1:87.4"
msgid ""
"Tepi tattha honti manomayā pītibhakkhā sayaṃpabhā antalikkhacarā "
"subhaṭṭhāyino, ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr ""
"There they too are mind-made, feeding on rapture, self-luminous, moving "
"through the sky, steadily glorious, and they remain like that for a very "
"long time."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="73"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:88.1"
msgid "Tatra, bhikkhave, yo so satto paṭhamaṃ upapanno tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "Now, the being who was reborn there first thinks:"

#. VAR: sajitā → sajjitā (s1-3, km) | sañjitā (pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:88.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahamasmi brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso vasavattī "
"issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘I am Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the Universal "
"Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, the Best, "
"the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been born and "
"those yet to be born."

msgctxt "dn1:88.3"
msgid "Mayā ime sattā nimmitā."
msgstr "These beings were created by me!"

msgctxt "dn1:88.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:88.5"
msgid "Mamañhi pubbe etadahosi:"
msgstr "Because first I thought:"

msgctxt "dn1:88.6"
msgid "“aho vata aññepi sattā itthattaṃ āgaccheyyun”ti."
msgstr "“Oh, if only another being would come to this state of existence.”"

# Correlation and causation!
#. VAR: mama ca → mamañca (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:88.7"
msgid "Iti mama ca manopaṇidhi, ime ca sattā itthattaṃ āgatā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Such was my heart’s wish, and then these creatures came to this state of "
"existence.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="74"></a>
#. VAR: upapannā → uppannā (si)
msgctxt "dn1:89.1"
msgid "Yepi te sattā pacchā upapannā, tesampi evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "And the beings who were reborn there later also think:"

msgctxt "dn1:89.2"
msgid ""
"‘ayaṃ kho bhavaṃ brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso "
"vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘This must be Brahmā, the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the "
"Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, "
"the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been "
"born and those yet to be born."

msgctxt "dn1:89.3"
msgid "Iminā mayaṃ bhotā brahmunā nimmitā."
msgstr "And we have been created by him."

msgctxt "dn1:89.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:89.5"
msgid ""
"Imañhi mayaṃ addasāma idha paṭhamaṃ upapannaṃ, mayaṃ panamha pacchā "
"upapannā’ti."
msgstr "Because we see that he was reborn here first, and we arrived later.’"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="75"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:90.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, yo so satto paṭhamaṃ upapanno, so dīghāyukataro ca hoti "
"vaṇṇavantataro ca mahesakkhataro ca."
msgstr ""
"And the being who was reborn first is more long-lived, beautiful, and "
"illustrious than those who arrived later."

msgctxt "dn1:90.2"
msgid ""
"Ye pana te sattā pacchā upapannā, te appāyukatarā ca honti dubbaṇṇatarā ca "
"appesakkhatarā ca."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="76"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:91.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, vijjati, yaṃ aññataro satto tamhā kāyā "
"cavitvā itthattaṃ āgacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that one of those beings passes away from that group and is "
"reborn in this state of existence."

msgctxt "dn1:91.2"
msgid "Itthattaṃ āgato samāno agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati."
msgstr "Having done so, they go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "dn1:91.3"
msgid ""
"Agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito samāno ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte taṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, tato "
"paraṃ nānussarati."
msgstr ""
"By dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus, "
"they experience a samādhi of the heart of such a kind that they recollect "
"that past life, but no further."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="77"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.19"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:92.1"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "dn1:92.2"
msgid ""
"‘yo kho so bhavaṃ brahmā mahābrahmā abhibhū anabhibhūto aññadatthudaso "
"vasavattī issaro kattā nimmātā seṭṭho sajitā vasī pitā bhūtabhabyānaṃ, yena "
"mayaṃ bhotā brahmunā nimmitā, so nicco dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo "
"sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassati."
msgstr ""
"‘He who is Brahmā—the Great Brahmā, the Undefeated, the Champion, the "
"Universal Seer, the Wielder of Power, the Lord God, the Maker, the Author, "
"the Best, the Begetter, the Controller, the Father of those who have been "
"born and those yet to be born—is permanent, everlasting, eternal, "
"imperishable, remaining the same for all eternity."

msgctxt "dn1:92.3"
msgid ""
"Ye pana mayaṃ ahumhā tena bhotā brahmunā nimmitā, te mayaṃ aniccā addhuvā "
"appāyukā cavanadhammā itthattaṃ āgatā’ti."
msgstr ""
"We who were created by that Brahmā are impermanent, not lasting, short-"
"lived, perishable, and have come to this state of existence."

#. VAR: Idaṃ → idaṃ kho (c1)
msgctxt "dn1:92.4"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the first ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are partially eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:92.5"
msgid "(1: 5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="78"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:93.1"
msgid ""
"Dutiye ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha ekaccasassatikā "
"ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca "
"paññapenti?"
msgstr "And what is the second ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:93.2"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, khiḍḍāpadosikā nāma devā, te ativelaṃ "
"hassakhiḍḍāratidhammasamāpannā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"There are gods named ‘depraved by play.’ They spend too much time laughing, "
"playing, and making merry."

#. VAR: sammussati → mussati (bj, pts1) | pamussati (s1-3)
msgctxt "dn1:93.3"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ ativelaṃ hassakhiḍḍāratidhammasamāpannānaṃ viharataṃ sati sammussati."
msgstr "And in doing so, they lose their mindfulness,"

msgctxt "dn1:93.4"
msgid "Satiyā sammosā te devā tamhā kāyā cavanti."
msgstr "and they pass away from that group of gods."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="79"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:94.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, vijjati yaṃ aññataro satto tamhā kāyā cavitvā "
"itthattaṃ āgacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that one of those beings passes away from that group and is "
"reborn in this state of existence."

msgctxt "dn1:94.2"
msgid "Itthattaṃ āgato samāno agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati."
msgstr "Having done so, they go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "dn1:94.3"
msgid ""
"Agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito samāno ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte taṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, tato "
"paraṃ nānussarati."
msgstr ""
"By dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus, "
"they experience a samādhi of the heart of such a kind that they recollect "
"that past life, but no further."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="80"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.20"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:95.1"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "dn1:95.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye kho te bhonto devā na khiḍḍāpadosikā, te na ativelaṃ "
"hassakhiḍḍāratidhammasamāpannā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"‘The gods not depraved by play don’t spend too much time laughing, playing, "
"and making merry."

msgctxt "dn1:95.3"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ na ativelaṃ hassakhiḍḍāratidhammasamāpannānaṃ viharataṃ sati na "
"sammussati."
msgstr "So they don’t lose their mindfulness,"

msgctxt "dn1:95.4"
msgid "Satiyā asammosā te devā tamhā kāyā na cavanti;"
msgstr "and don’t pass away from that group of gods."

msgctxt "dn1:95.5"
msgid "niccā dhuvā sassatā avipariṇāmadhammā sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"They are permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, remaining the same "
"for all eternity."

msgctxt "dn1:95.6"
msgid ""
"Ye pana mayaṃ ahumhā khiḍḍāpadosikā, te mayaṃ ativelaṃ "
"hassakhiḍḍāratidhammasamāpannā viharimhā."
msgstr ""
"But we who were depraved by play spent too much time laughing, playing, and "
"making merry."

msgctxt "dn1:95.7"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ no ativelaṃ hassakhiḍḍāratidhammasamāpannānaṃ viharataṃ sati "
"sammussati."
msgstr "In doing so, we lost our mindfulness,"

msgctxt "dn1:95.8"
msgid ""
"Satiyā sammosā evaṃ mayaṃ tamhā kāyā cutā aniccā addhuvā appāyukā "
"cavanadhammā itthattaṃ āgatā’ti."
msgstr ""
"and passed away from that group of gods. We are impermanent, not lasting, "
"short-lived, perishable, and have come to this state of existence.’"

msgctxt "dn1:95.9"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the second ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are partially eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:95.10"
msgid "(2: 6)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="81"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:96.1"
msgid ""
"Tatiye ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha ekaccasassatikā "
"ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca "
"paññapenti?"
msgstr "And what is the third ground on which they rely?"

# The parallel with khiddapadosika rather confuses the issue, suggesting a rendering "depraved in mind" here. However elsewhere in the suttas, manopadosa consistently means "malicious intent", MN 56, MN 93, also see mano padūseyya at MN 21 and MN 28. Thus the contrast here would seem to be greed vs hate. Also note DN 26, "tesaṃ sattānaṃ aññamaññamhi tibbo āghāto paccupaṭṭhito bhavissati tibbo byāpādo tibbo manopadoso tibbaṃ vadhakacittaṃ." 
msgctxt "dn1:96.2"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, manopadosikā nāma devā, te ativelaṃ aññamaññaṃ "
"upanijjhāyanti."
msgstr ""
"There are gods named ‘malevolent’. They spend too much time gazing at each "
"other,"

msgctxt "dn1:96.3"
msgid "Te ativelaṃ aññamaññaṃ upanijjhāyantā aññamaññamhi cittāni padūsenti."
msgstr "so they grow angry with each other,"

msgctxt "dn1:96.4"
msgid "Te aññamaññaṃ paduṭṭhacittā kilantakāyā kilantacittā."
msgstr "and their bodies and minds get tired."

msgctxt "dn1:96.5"
msgid "Te devā tamhā kāyā cavanti."
msgstr "They pass away from that group of gods."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="82"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:97.1"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, vijjati yaṃ aññataro satto tamhā kāyā cavitvā "
"itthattaṃ āgacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that one of those beings passes away from that group and is "
"reborn in this state of existence."

msgctxt "dn1:97.2"
msgid "Itthattaṃ āgato samāno agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati."
msgstr "Having done so, they go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "dn1:97.3"
msgid ""
"Agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito samāno ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte taṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, tato "
"paraṃ nānussarati."
msgstr ""
"By dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus, "
"they experience a samādhi of the heart of such a kind that they recollect "
"that past life, but no further."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="83"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.21"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:98.1"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "dn1:98.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye kho te bhonto devā na manopadosikā, te nātivelaṃ aññamaññaṃ "
"upanijjhāyanti."
msgstr ""
"‘The gods who are not malevolent don’t spend too much time gazing at each "
"other,"

msgctxt "dn1:98.3"
msgid ""
"Te nātivelaṃ aññamaññaṃ upanijjhāyantā aññamaññamhi cittāni nappadūsenti."
msgstr "so they don’t grow angry with each other,"

msgctxt "dn1:98.4"
msgid "Te aññamaññaṃ appaduṭṭhacittā akilantakāyā akilantacittā."
msgstr "their bodies and minds don’t get tired,"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn1:98.5"
msgid ""
"Te devā tamhā kāyā na cavanti, niccā dhuvā sassatā avipariṇāmadhammā "
"sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassanti."
msgstr ""
"and they don’t pass away from that group of gods. They are permanent, "
"everlasting, eternal, imperishable, remaining the same for all eternity."

msgctxt "dn1:98.6"
msgid ""
"Ye pana mayaṃ ahumhā manopadosikā, te mayaṃ ativelaṃ aññamaññaṃ "
"upanijjhāyimhā."
msgstr "But we who were malevolent spent too much time gazing at each other,"

msgctxt "dn1:98.7"
msgid ""
"Te mayaṃ ativelaṃ aññamaññaṃ upanijjhāyantā aññamaññamhi cittāni padūsimhā, "
"te mayaṃ aññamaññaṃ paduṭṭhacittā kilantakāyā kilantacittā."
msgstr "we grew angry with each other, our bodies and minds got tired,"

msgctxt "dn1:98.8"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ mayaṃ tamhā kāyā cutā aniccā addhuvā appāyukā cavanadhammā itthattaṃ "
"āgatā’ti."
msgstr ""
"and we passed away from that group of gods. We are impermanent, not lasting, "
"short-lived, perishable, and have come to this state of existence.’"

msgctxt "dn1:98.9"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the third ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are partially eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:98.10"
msgid "(3: 7)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="84"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:99.1"
msgid ""
"Catutthe ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha ekaccasassatikā "
"ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca "
"paññapenti?"
msgstr "And what is the fourth ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:99.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā takkī hoti vīmaṃsī."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin relies on logic and inquiry. They speak of "
"what they have worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, expressing "
"their own perspective:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn1:99.3"
msgid "So takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānaṃ evamāha:"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "dn1:99.4"
msgid ""
"‘yaṃ kho idaṃ vuccati cakkhuṃ itipi sotaṃ itipi ghānaṃ itipi jivhā itipi "
"kāyo itipi, ayaṃ attā anicco addhuvo asassato vipariṇāmadhammo."
msgstr ""
"‘That which is called “the eye” or “the ear” or “the nose” or “the tongue” "
"or “the body”: that self is impermanent, not lasting, transient, perishable"

msgctxt "dn1:99.5"
msgid ""
"Yañca kho idaṃ vuccati cittanti vā manoti vā viññāṇanti vā ayaṃ attā nicco "
"dhuvo sassato avipariṇāmadhammo sassatisamaṃ tatheva ṭhassatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"That which is called “mind” or “sentience” or “consciousness”: that self is "
"permanent, everlasting, eternal, imperishable, remaining the same for all "
"eternity.’"

msgctxt "dn1:99.6"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos are partially eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:99.7"
msgid "(4: 8)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="85"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:100.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ekaccasassatikā ekaccaasassatikā "
"ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti catūhi "
"vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the four grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins assert that "
"the self and the cosmos are partially eternal and partially not eternal."

msgctxt "dn1:100.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ekaccasassatikā "
"ekaccaasassatikā ekaccaṃ sassataṃ ekaccaṃ asassataṃ attānañca lokañca "
"paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva catūhi vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena;"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who assert that the self and the cosmos are "
"partially eternal and partially not eternal do so on one or other of these "
"four grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:100.3"
msgid "natthi ito bahiddhā."
msgstr "Outside of this there is none."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="86"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.22"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:101.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato pajānāti:"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn1:101.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime diṭṭhiṭṭhānā evaṅgahitā evaṃparāmaṭṭhā evaṅgatikā bhavanti "
"evaṃabhisamparāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If you hold on to and attach to these grounds for views it leads to such "
"and such a destiny in the next life.’ He understands this, and what goes "
"beyond this."

msgctxt "dn1:101.3"
msgid ""
"Tañca tathāgato pajānāti, tato ca uttaritaraṃ pajānāti, tañca pajānanaṃ na "
"parāmasati, aparāmasato cassa paccattaññeva nibbuti viditā."
msgstr ""
"Yet since he does not misapprehend that understanding, he has realized "
"extinguishment within himself."

msgctxt "dn1:101.4"
msgid ""
"Vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca "
"yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto, bhikkhave, tathāgato."
msgstr ""
"Having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback and "
"escape from feelings, the Realized One is freed through not grasping."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="87"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:102.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā "
"atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are the principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, "
"sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—"
"which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own "
"insight. And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak "
"of these things."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:103.1"
msgid "3.1.3. Antānantavāda"
msgstr "The Cosmos is Finite or Infinite"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="88"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:104.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā antānantikā antānantaṃ lokassa "
"paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who theorize about size, and assert "
"that the cosmos is finite or infinite on four grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:104.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha antānantikā antānantaṃ "
"lokassa paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the four grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="89"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:105.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte antasaññī lokasmiṃ viharati."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin—by dint of keen, resolute, committed, and "
"diligent effort, and right focus—experiences a samādhi of the heart of such "
"a kind that they meditate perceiving the cosmos as finite."

