"that the cosmos is finite or infinite."

msgctxt "dn1:110.13"
msgid "(3: 11)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="95"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.24"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:111.1"
msgid ""
"Catutthe ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha antānantikā "
"antānantaṃ lokassa paññapenti?"
msgstr "And what is the fourth ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:111.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā takkī hoti vīmaṃsī."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin relies on logic and inquiry. They speak of "
"what they have worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, expressing "
"their own perspective:"

msgctxt "dn1:111.3"
msgid "So takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānaṃ evamāha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:111.4"
msgid "‘nevāyaṃ loko antavā, na panānanto."
msgstr "‘The cosmos is neither finite nor infinite."

msgctxt "dn1:111.5"
msgid "Ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "The ascetics and brahmins who say that"

msgctxt "dn1:111.6"
msgid "“antavā ayaṃ loko parivaṭumo”ti, tesaṃ musā."
msgstr "the cosmos is finite are wrong,"

msgctxt "dn1:111.7"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "as are those who say that"

msgctxt "dn1:111.8"
msgid "“ananto ayaṃ loko apariyanto”ti, tesampi musā."
msgstr "the cosmos is infinite,"

msgctxt "dn1:111.9"
msgid "Yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "and those who say that"

msgctxt "dn1:111.10"
msgid "“antavā ca ayaṃ loko ananto cā”ti, tesampi musā."
msgstr "the cosmos is both finite and infinite."

msgctxt "dn1:111.11"
msgid "Nevāyaṃ loko antavā, na panānanto’ti."
msgstr "The cosmos is neither finite nor infinite."

msgctxt "dn1:111.12"
msgid ""
