"antānantikā antānantaṃ lokassa paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the cosmos is finite or infinite."

msgctxt "dn1:111.13"
msgid "(4: 12)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="96"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:112.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā antānantikā antānantaṃ lokassa "
"paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the four grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins assert that "
"the cosmos is finite or infinite."

msgctxt "dn1:112.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā antānantikā antānantaṃ lokassa "
"paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva catūhi vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena;"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who assert that the cosmos is finite or infinite "
"do so on one or other of these four grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:112.3"
msgid "natthi ito bahiddhā."
msgstr "Outside of this there is none."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="97"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:113.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato pajānāti:"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this:"

msgctxt "dn1:113.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime diṭṭhiṭṭhānā evaṅgahitā evaṃparāmaṭṭhā evaṅgatikā bhavanti "
"evaṃabhisamparāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If you hold on to and attach to these grounds for views it leads to such "
"and such a destiny in the next life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:113.3"
msgid ""
"Tañca tathāgato pajānāti, tato ca uttaritaraṃ pajānāti, tañca pajānanaṃ na "
"parāmasati, aparāmasato cassa paccattaññeva nibbuti viditā."
msgstr ""
"He understands this, and what goes beyond this. Yet since he does not "
"misapprehend that understanding, he has realized extinguishment within "
"himself."

msgctxt "dn1:113.4"
msgid ""
"Vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca "
"yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto, bhikkhave, tathāgato."
msgstr ""
"Having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback and "
"escape from feelings, the Realized One is freed through not grasping."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="98"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:114.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā "
"atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are the principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, "
"sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—"
"which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own "
"insight. And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak "
"of these things."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:115.1"
msgid "3.1.4. Amarāvikkhepavāda"
msgstr "Equivocators"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="99"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:116.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā amarāvikkhepikā, tattha tattha pañhaṃ "
"puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ catūhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who are equivocators. Whenever they’re "
"asked a question, they resort to evasiveness and equivocation on four "
"grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:116.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha amarāvikkhepikā tattha "
"tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ catūhi "
"vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the four grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="100"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.25"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:117.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ‘idaṃ kusalan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānāti, ‘idaṃ akusalan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin doesn’t truly understand what is skillful "
"and what is unskillful."

msgctxt "dn1:117.2"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think: "

msgctxt "dn1:117.3"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho “idaṃ kusalan”ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi, “idaṃ akusalan”ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi."
msgstr "‘I don’t truly understand what is skillful and what is unskillful. "

msgctxt "dn1:117.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañce kho pana “idaṃ kusalan”ti yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto, “idaṃ akusalan”ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto, “idaṃ kusalan”ti vā byākareyyaṃ, “idaṃ akusalan”ti "
"vā byākareyyaṃ, taṃ mamassa musā."
msgstr ""
"If I was to declare that something was skillful or unskillful I might be "
"wrong."

msgctxt "dn1:117.5"
msgid "Yaṃ mamassa musā, so mamassa vighāto."
msgstr "That would be stressful for me,"

msgctxt "dn1:117.6"
msgid "Yo mamassa vighāto so mamassa antarāyo’ti."
msgstr "and that stress would be an obstacle.’"

msgctxt "dn1:117.7"
msgid ""
"Iti so musāvādabhayā musāvādaparijegucchā nevidaṃ kusalanti byākaroti, na "
"panidaṃ akusalanti byākaroti, tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno "
"vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjati amarāvikkhepaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"So from fear and disgust with false speech they avoid stating whether "
"something is skillful or unskillful. Whenever they’re asked a question, they "
"resort to evasiveness and equivocation:"

msgctxt "dn1:117.8"
msgid "‘evantipi me no;"
msgstr ""
"‘I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s "
"otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so.’"

