"tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the third ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:119.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā ‘idaṃ kusalan’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"nappajānāti, ‘idaṃ akusalan’ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin doesn’t truly understand what is skillful "
"and what is unskillful."

msgctxt "dn1:119.3"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think: "

msgctxt "dn1:119.4"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ kho “idaṃ kusalan”ti yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi, “idaṃ akusalan”ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ nappajānāmi."
msgstr "‘I don’t truly understand what is skillful and what is unskillful. "

msgctxt "dn1:119.5"
msgid ""
"Ahañce kho pana “idaṃ kusalan”ti yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto “idaṃ akusalan”ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ appajānanto “idaṃ kusalan”ti vā byākareyyaṃ, “idaṃ akusalan”ti "
"vā byākareyyaṃ;"
msgstr "Suppose I was to declare that something was skillful or unskillful."

#. VAR: bhindantā → vobhindantā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "dn1:119.6"
msgid ""
"santi hi kho samaṇabrāhmaṇā paṇḍitā nipuṇā kataparappavādā vālavedhirūpā, te "
"bhindantā maññe caranti paññāgatena diṭṭhigatāni, te maṃ tattha "
"samanuyuñjeyyuṃ samanugāheyyuṃ samanubhāseyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"There are clever ascetics and brahmins who are subtle, accomplished in the "
"doctrines of others, hair-splitters. You’d think they live to demolish "
"convictions with their intellect. They might question, press, and examine me "
"about that."

msgctxt "dn1:119.7"
msgid ""
"Ye maṃ tattha samanuyuñjeyyuṃ samanugāheyyuṃ samanubhāseyyuṃ, tesāhaṃ na "
"sampāyeyyaṃ."
msgstr "I’d be stumped by such examination."

msgctxt "dn1:119.8"
msgid "Yesāhaṃ na sampāyeyyaṃ, so mamassa vighāto."
msgstr "That would be stressful for me,"

msgctxt "dn1:119.9"
msgid "Yo mamassa vighāto, so mamassa antarāyo’ti."
msgstr "and that stress would be an obstacle.’"

msgctxt "dn1:119.10"
msgid ""
"Iti so anuyogabhayā anuyogaparijegucchā nevidaṃ kusalanti byākaroti, na "
"panidaṃ akusalanti byākaroti, tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno "
"vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjati amarāvikkhepaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"So from fear and disgust with examination they avoid stating whether "
"something is skillful or unskillful. Whenever they’re asked a question, they "
"resort to evasiveness and equivocation:"

msgctxt "dn1:119.11"
msgid "‘evantipi me no;"
msgstr ""
"‘I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s "
"otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t deny it’s not so.’"

msgctxt "dn1:119.12"
msgid "tathātipi me no;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:119.13"
msgid "aññathātipi me no;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:119.14"
msgid "notipi me no;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:119.15"
msgid "no notipi me no’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:119.16"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"amarāvikkhepikā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti "
"amarāvikkhepaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This is the third ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to resort "
"to evasiveness and equivocation."

msgctxt "dn1:119.17"
msgid "(3: 15)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="103"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:120.1"
msgid ""
"Catutthe ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha amarāvikkhepikā "
"tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the fourth ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:120.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā mando hoti momūho."
msgstr "It’s when some ascetic or brahmin is dull and stupid."

msgctxt "dn1:120.3"
msgid ""
"So mandattā momūhattā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭho samāno vācāvikkhepaṃ "
"āpajjati amarāvikkhepaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Because of that, whenever they’re asked a question, they resort to "
"evasiveness and equivocation:"

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn1:120.4"
msgid ""
"‘atthi paro loko’ti iti ce maṃ pucchasi, ‘atthi paro loko’ti iti ce me assa, "
"‘atthi paro loko’ti iti te naṃ byākareyyaṃ, ‘evantipi me no, tathātipi me "
"no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi me no’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Suppose you were to ask me whether there is another world. If I believed "
"there was, I would say so. But I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t say it’s "
"like that. I don’t say it’s otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And I don’t "
"deny it’s not so."

msgctxt "dn1:120.5"
msgid "‘Natthi paro loko …"
msgstr "Suppose you were to ask me whether there is no other world …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.7"
msgid "‘atthi ca natthi ca paro loko …"
msgstr "whether there both is and is not another world …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.8"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.9"
msgid "‘nevatthi na natthi paro loko …"
msgstr "whether there neither is nor is not another world …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.10"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.11"
msgid "‘atthi sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr "whether there are beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.12"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.13"
msgid "‘natthi sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr "whether there are no beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.14"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.15"
msgid "‘atthi ca natthi ca sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr ""
"whether there both are and are not beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.16"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.17"
msgid "‘nevatthi na natthi sattā opapātikā …"
msgstr ""
"whether there neither are nor are not beings who are reborn spontaneously …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.18"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.19"
msgid "‘atthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr "whether there is fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.20"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.21"
msgid "‘natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr "whether there is no fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.22"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.23"
msgid "‘atthi ca natthi ca sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr ""
"whether there both is and is not fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.24"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.25"
msgid "‘nevatthi na natthi sukatadukkaṭānaṃ kammānaṃ phalaṃ vipāko …"
msgstr ""
"whether there neither is nor is not fruit and result of good and bad deeds …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.26"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.27"
msgid "‘hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "whether a Realized One exists after death …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.28"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.29"
msgid "‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "whether a Realized One doesn’t exist after death …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.30"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: hoti ca na ca hoti → hoti ca na hoti ca (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "dn1:120.31"
msgid "‘hoti ca na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā …"
msgstr "whether a Realized One both exists and doesn’t exist after death …"

msgctxt "dn1:120.32"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:120.33"
msgid ""
"‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti iti ce maṃ pucchasi, ‘neva "
"hoti na na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti iti ce me assa, ‘neva hoti na na "
"hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti iti te naṃ byākareyyaṃ, ‘evantipi me no, "
"tathātipi me no, aññathātipi me no, notipi me no, no notipi me no’ti."
msgstr ""
"whether a Realized One neither exists nor doesn’t exist after death. If I "
"believed there was, I would say so. But I don’t say it’s like this. I don’t "
"say it’s like that. I don’t say it’s otherwise. I don’t say it’s not so. And "
"I don’t deny it’s not so."

msgctxt "dn1:120.34"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, catutthaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"amarāvikkhepikā tattha tattha pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti "
"amarāvikkhepaṃ."
msgstr ""
"This is the fourth ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to resort "
"to evasiveness and equivocation."

msgctxt "dn1:120.35"
msgid "(4: 16)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="104"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.28"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:121.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā amarāvikkhepikā tattha tattha pañhaṃ "
"puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ catūhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the four grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins who are "
"equivocators resort to evasiveness and equivocation whenever they’re asked a "
"question."

#, fuzzy
msgctxt "dn1:121.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā amarāvikkhepikā tattha tattha "
"pañhaṃ puṭṭhā samānā vācāvikkhepaṃ āpajjanti amarāvikkhepaṃ, sabbe te "
"imeheva catūhi vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena, natthi ito bahiddhā …"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who resort to equivocation do so on one or other "
"of these four grounds. Outside of this there is none."

msgctxt "dn1:121.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this …"

msgctxt "dn1:121.4"
msgid "yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these "
"things."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:122.1"
msgid "3.1.5. Adhiccasamuppannavāda"
msgstr "Doctrines of Origination by Chance"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="105"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:123.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā adhiccasamuppannikā adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"attānañca lokañca paññapenti dvīhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who theorize about chance. They assert "
"that the self and the cosmos arose by chance on two grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:123.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha adhiccasamuppannikā "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti dvīhi vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the two grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="106"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.29"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:124.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, asaññasattā nāma devā."
msgstr "There are gods named ‘non-percipient beings’."

msgctxt "dn1:124.2"
msgid "Saññuppādā ca pana te devā tamhā kāyā cavanti."
msgstr "When perception arises they pass away from that group of gods."

msgctxt "dn1:124.3"
msgid ""
"Ṭhānaṃ kho panetaṃ, bhikkhave, vijjati, yaṃ aññataro satto tamhā kāyā "
"cavitvā itthattaṃ āgacchati."
msgstr ""
"It’s possible that one of those beings passes away from that group and is "
"reborn in this state of existence."

msgctxt "dn1:124.4"
msgid "Itthattaṃ āgato samāno agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajati."
msgstr "Having done so, they go forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "dn1:124.5"
msgid ""
"Agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito samāno ātappamanvāya padhānamanvāya "
"anuyogamanvāya appamādamanvāya sammāmanasikāramanvāya tathārūpaṃ "
"cetosamādhiṃ phusati, yathāsamāhite citte saññuppādaṃ anussarati, tato paraṃ "
"nānussarati."
msgstr ""
"By dint of keen, resolute, committed, and diligent effort, and right focus, "
"they experience a samādhi of the heart of such a kind that they recollect "
"the arising of perception, but no further."

msgctxt "dn1:124.6"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "dn1:124.7"
msgid "‘adhiccasamuppanno attā ca loko ca."
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos arose by chance."

msgctxt "dn1:124.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:124.9"
msgid "Ahañhi pubbe nāhosiṃ, somhi etarahi ahutvā santatāya pariṇato’ti."
msgstr ""
"Because formerly I didn’t exist. Now from not being I’ve changed into being.’"

msgctxt "dn1:124.10"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"adhiccasamuppannikā adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the first ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos arose by chance."

msgctxt "dn1:124.11"
msgid "(1: 17)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="107"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:125.1"
msgid ""
"Dutiye ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha adhiccasamuppannikā "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti?"
msgstr "And what is the second ground on which they rely?"

msgctxt "dn1:125.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā takkī hoti vīmaṃsī."
msgstr ""
"It’s when some ascetic or brahmin relies on logic and inquiry. They speak of "
"what they have worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, expressing "
"their own perspective:"

msgctxt "dn1:125.3"
msgid "So takkapariyāhataṃ vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ sayampaṭibhānaṃ evamāha:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "dn1:125.4"
msgid "‘adhiccasamuppanno attā ca loko cā’ti."
msgstr "‘The self and the cosmos arose by chance.’"

msgctxt "dn1:125.5"
msgid ""
"Idaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyaṃ ṭhānaṃ, yaṃ āgamma yaṃ ārabbha eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā "
"adhiccasamuppannikā adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"This is the second ground on which some ascetics and brahmins rely to assert "
"that the self and the cosmos arose by chance."

msgctxt "dn1:125.6"
msgid "(2: 18)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="108"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:126.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā adhiccasamuppannikā "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti dvīhi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the two grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins who theorize "
"about chance assert that the self and the cosmos arose by chance."

msgctxt "dn1:126.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā adhiccasamuppannikā "
"adhiccasamuppannaṃ attānañca lokañca paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva dvīhi "
"vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena, natthi ito bahiddhā …"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who theorize about do so on one or other of these "
"two grounds. Outside of this there is none."

msgctxt "dn1:126.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this …"

msgctxt "dn1:126.4"
msgid "yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these "
"things."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="109"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:127.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā pubbantānudiṭṭhino "
"pubbantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti aṭṭhārasahi "
"vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the eighteen grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins who "
"theorize about the past assert various hypotheses concerning the past."

msgctxt "dn1:127.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā pubbantakappikā "
"pubbantānudiṭṭhino pubbantamārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni "
"abhivadanti, sabbe te imeheva aṭṭhārasahi vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena, "
"natthi ito bahiddhā."
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past do so on one or other "
"of these eighteen grounds. Outside of this there is none."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="110"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:128.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato pajānāti:"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this:"

msgctxt "dn1:128.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime diṭṭhiṭṭhānā evaṅgahitā evaṃparāmaṭṭhā evaṅgatikā bhavanti "
"evaṃabhisamparāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If you hold on to and attach to these grounds for views it leads to such "
"and such a destiny in the next life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:128.3"
msgid ""
"Tañca tathāgato pajānāti, tato ca uttaritaraṃ pajānāti, tañca pajānanaṃ na "
"parāmasati, aparāmasato cassa paccattaññeva nibbuti viditā."
msgstr ""
"Yet since he does not misapprehend that understanding, he has realized "
"extinguishment within himself."

msgctxt "dn1:128.4"
msgid ""
"Vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca "
"yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto, bhikkhave, tathāgato."
msgstr ""
"Having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback and "
"escape from feelings, the Realized One is freed through not grasping."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="111"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.30"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:129.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā "
"atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are the principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, "
"sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—"
"which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own "
"insight. And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak "
"of these things."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "dn1:130.1"
msgid "Dutiyabhāṇavāro."
msgstr ""

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:131.1"
msgid "3.2. Aparantakappika"
msgstr "Theories About the Future"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="112"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:132.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino, "
"aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti catucattārīsāya "
"vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the future, and "
"assert various hypotheses concerning the future on forty-four grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:132.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha aparantakappikā "
"aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni "
"abhivadanti catucattārīsāya vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the forty-four grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:133.1"
msgid "3.2.1. Saññīvāda"
msgstr "Percipient Life After Death"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="113"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.31"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:134.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā uddhamāghātanikā saññīvādā "
"uddhamāghātanaṃ saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti soḷasahi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who say there is life after death, and "
"assert that the self lives on after death in a percipient form on sixteen "
"grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:134.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha uddhamāghātanikā saññīvādā "
"uddhamāghātanaṃ saññiṃ attānaṃ paññapenti soḷasahi vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the sixteen grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="114"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:135.1"
msgid "‘Rūpī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā saññī’ti naṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"They assert: ‘The self is percipient and sound after death, and it is "
