"viññāṇan”ti viññāṇañcāyatanūpago."
msgstr ""
"There is another self which has gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"infinite space. Aware that “consciousness is infinite”, it’s reborn in the "
"dimension of infinite consciousness."

msgctxt "dn1:180.5"
msgid "Taṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi."
msgstr "You don’t know or see that."

msgctxt "dn1:180.6"
msgid "Tamahaṃ jānāmi passāmi."
msgstr "But I know it and see it."

msgctxt "dn1:180.7"
msgid ""
"So kho, bho, attā yato kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ "
"maraṇā, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā sammā samucchinno hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Since this self is annihilated and destroyed when the body breaks up, and "
"doesn’t exist after death, that’s how this self becomes rightly annihilated.’"

msgctxt "dn1:180.8"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr "That is how some assert the annihilation of an existing being."

msgctxt "dn1:180.9"
msgid "(5: 55)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="157"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:181.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says to them:"

msgctxt "dn1:181.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, so attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi;"
msgstr "‘<em>That</em> self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it."

msgctxt "dn1:181.3"
msgid "no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā sammā samucchinno hoti."
msgstr "But that’s not how this self becomes rightly annihilated."

msgctxt "dn1:181.4"
msgid ""
"Atthi kho, bho, añño attā sabbaso viññāṇañcāyatanaṃ samatikkamma “natthi "
"kiñcī”ti ākiñcaññāyatanūpago."
msgstr ""
"There is another self that has gone totally beyond the dimension of infinite "
"consciousness. Aware that “there is nothing at all”, it’s been reborn in the "
"dimension of nothingness."

msgctxt "dn1:181.5"
msgid "Taṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi."
msgstr "You don’t know or see that."

msgctxt "dn1:181.6"
msgid "Tamahaṃ jānāmi passāmi."
msgstr "But I know it and see it."

msgctxt "dn1:181.7"
msgid ""
"So kho, bho, attā yato kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ "
"maraṇā, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā sammā samucchinno hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Since this self is annihilated and destroyed when the body breaks up, and "
"doesn’t exist after death, that’s how this self becomes rightly annihilated.’"

msgctxt "dn1:181.8"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr "That is how some assert the annihilation of an existing being."

msgctxt "dn1:181.9"
msgid "(6: 56)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="158"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:182.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says to them:"

msgctxt "dn1:182.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, eso attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi;"
msgstr "‘<em>That</em> self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it."

msgctxt "dn1:182.3"
msgid "no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā sammā samucchinno hoti."
msgstr "But that’s not how <em>this</em> self becomes rightly annihilated."

msgctxt "dn1:182.4"
msgid ""
"Atthi kho, bho, añño attā sabbaso ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ samatikkamma “santametaṃ "
"paṇītametan”ti nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpago."
msgstr ""
"There is another self that has gone totally beyond the dimension of "
"nothingness. Aware that “this is peaceful, this is sublime”, it’s been "
"reborn in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception."

msgctxt "dn1:182.5"
msgid "Taṃ tvaṃ na jānāsi na passasi."
msgstr "You don’t know or see that."

msgctxt "dn1:182.6"
msgid "Tamahaṃ jānāmi passāmi."
msgstr "But I know it and see it."

msgctxt "dn1:182.7"
msgid ""
"So kho, bho, attā yato kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ "
"maraṇā, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā sammā samucchinno hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Since this self is annihilated and destroyed when the body breaks up, and "
"doesn’t exist after death, that’s how this self becomes rightly annihilated.’"

msgctxt "dn1:182.8"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr "That is how some assert the annihilation of an existing being."

msgctxt "dn1:182.9"
msgid "(7: 57)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="159"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.36"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:183.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā ucchedavādā sato sattassa ucchedaṃ "
"vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti sattahi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the seven grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins assert the "
"annihilation, eradication, and extermination of an existing being."

msgctxt "dn1:183.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā ucchedavādā sato sattassa "
"ucchedaṃ vināsaṃ vibhavaṃ paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva sattahi vatthūhi …"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who assert the annihilation, eradication, and "
"extermination of an existing being do so on one or other of these eight "
"grounds. Outside of this there is none."

msgctxt "dn1:183.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this …"

msgctxt "dn1:183.4"
msgid "yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these "
"things."

#. </p><h4>
msgctxt "dn1:184.1"
msgid "3.2.5. Diṭṭhadhammanibbānavāda"
msgstr "Extinguishment in the Present Life"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="160"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:185.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato sattassa "
"paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"There are some ascetics and brahmins who speak of extinguishment in the "
"present life. They assert the ultimate extinguishment of an existing being "
"in the present life on five grounds."

msgctxt "dn1:185.2"
msgid ""
"Te ca bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā kimāgamma kimārabbha diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā "
"sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi?"
msgstr "And what are the five grounds on which they rely?"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="161"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:186.1"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco samaṇo vā brāhmaṇo vā evaṃvādī hoti evaṃdiṭṭhi:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "dn1:186.2"
msgid ""
"‘yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto "
"paricāreti, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto "
"hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘When this self amuses itself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of "
"sensual stimulation, that’s how this self attains ultimate extinguishment in "
"the present life.’"

msgctxt "dn1:186.3"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:186.4"
msgid "(1: 58)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="162"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.37"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:187.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says to them:"

msgctxt "dn1:187.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, eso attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi;"
msgstr "‘<em>That</em> self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it."

msgctxt "dn1:187.3"
msgid ""
"no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr ""
"But that’s not how <em>this</em> self attains ultimate extinguishment in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:187.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:187.5"
msgid ""
"Kāmā hi, bho, aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, tesaṃ vipariṇāmaññathābhāvā "
"uppajjanti sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā."
msgstr ""
"Because sensual pleasures are impermanent, suffering, and perishable. Their "
"decay and perishing give rise to sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, and "
"distress."

msgctxt "dn1:187.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi "
"savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja "
"viharati, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto "
"hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unwholesome qualities, "
"this self enters and remains in the first absorption, which has the rapture "
"and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it "
"connected. That’s how this self attains ultimate extinguishment in the "
"present life.’"

msgctxt "dn1:187.7"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:187.8"
msgid "(2: 59)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="163"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:188.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says to them:"

msgctxt "dn1:188.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, eso attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi;"
msgstr "‘<em>That</em> self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it."

msgctxt "dn1:188.3"
msgid ""
"no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr ""
"But that’s not how <em>this</em> self attains ultimate extinguishment in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:188.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:188.5"
msgid "Yadeva tattha vitakkitaṃ vicāritaṃ, etenetaṃ oḷārikaṃ akkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"Because the placing of the mind and the keeping it in place there are coarse."

msgctxt "dn1:188.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ "
"cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharati, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā "
"paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"But when the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, this "
"self enters and remains in the second absorption, which has the rapture and "
"bliss born of samādhi, with internal clarity and confidence, and unified "
"mind, without placing the mind and keeping it connected. That’s how this "
"self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life.’"

msgctxt "dn1:188.7"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:188.8"
msgid "(3: 60)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="164"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:189.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says to them:"

msgctxt "dn1:189.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, eso attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi;"
msgstr "‘<em>That</em> self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it."

msgctxt "dn1:189.3"
msgid ""
"no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr ""
"But that’s not how <em>this</em> self attains ultimate extinguishment in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:189.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:189.5"
msgid ""
"Yadeva tattha pītigataṃ cetaso uppilāvitattaṃ, etenetaṃ oḷārikaṃ akkhāyati."
msgstr "Because the rapture and emotional excitement there are coarse."

msgctxt "dn1:189.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca viharati, sato ca "
"sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedeti, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti “"
"upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī”ti, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, "
"ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"But with the fading away of rapture, this self enters and remains in the "
"third absorption, where it meditates with equanimity, mindful and aware, "
"personally experiencing the bliss of which the noble ones declare, “"
"Equanimous and mindful, one meditates in bliss”. That’s how this self "
"attains ultimate extinguishment in the present life.’"

msgctxt "dn1:189.7"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:189.8"
msgid "(4: 61)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="165"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.38"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:190.1"
msgid "Tamañño evamāha:"
msgstr "But someone else says to them:"

msgctxt "dn1:190.2"
msgid "‘atthi kho, bho, eso attā, yaṃ tvaṃ vadesi, neso natthīti vadāmi;"
msgstr "‘That self of which you speak does exist, I don’t deny it."

msgctxt "dn1:190.3"
msgid ""
"no ca kho, bho, ayaṃ attā ettāvatā paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr ""
"But that’s not how this self attains ultimate extinguishment in the present "
"life."

msgctxt "dn1:190.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "dn1:190.5"
msgid "Yadeva tattha sukhamiti cetaso ābhogo, etenetaṃ oḷārikaṃ akkhāyati."
msgstr "Because the bliss and enjoyment there are coarse."

msgctxt "dn1:190.6"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bho, ayaṃ attā sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva "
"somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ "
"catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati, ettāvatā kho, bho, ayaṃ attā "
"paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ patto hotī’ti."
msgstr ""
"But giving up pleasure and pain, and ending former happiness and sadness, "
"this self enters and remains in the fourth absorption, without pleasure or "
"pain, with pure equanimity and mindfulness. That’s how this self attains "
"ultimate extinguishment in the present life.’"

msgctxt "dn1:190.7"
msgid "Ittheke sato sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"That is how some assert the extinguishment of an existing being in the "
"present life."

msgctxt "dn1:190.8"
msgid "(5: 62)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="166"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:191.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato "
"sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti pañcahi vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the five grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins assert the "
"ultimate extinguishment of an existing being in the present life."

msgctxt "dn1:191.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā diṭṭhadhammanibbānavādā sato "
"sattassa paramadiṭṭhadhammanibbānaṃ paññapenti, sabbe te imeheva pañcahi "
"vatthūhi …"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who assert the ultimate extinguishment of an "
"existing being in the present life do so on one or other of these five "
"grounds. Outside of this there is none."

msgctxt "dn1:191.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this …"

msgctxt "dn1:191.4"
msgid "yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these "
"things."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="167"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.39"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:192.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā aparantakappikā aparantānudiṭṭhino "
"aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti catucattārīsāya "
"vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the forty-four grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins who "
"theorize about the future assert various hypotheses concerning the future."

msgctxt "dn1:192.2"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā aparantakappikā "
"aparantānudiṭṭhino aparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni "
"abhivadanti, sabbe te imeheva catucattārīsāya vatthūhi …"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the future do so on one or "
"other of these forty-four grounds. Outside of this there is none."

msgctxt "dn1:192.3"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this …"

msgctxt "dn1:192.4"
msgid "yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak of these "
"things."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="168"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:193.1"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho te, bhikkhave, samaṇabrāhmaṇā pubbantakappikā ca aparantakappikā "
"ca pubbantāparantakappikā ca pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino pubbantāparantaṃ "
"ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi."
msgstr ""
"These are the sixty-two grounds on which those ascetics and brahmins who "
"theorize about the past and the future assert various hypotheses concerning "
"the past and the future."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="169"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:194.1"
msgid ""
"Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā pubbantakappikā vā "
"aparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantakappikā vā pubbantāparantānudiṭṭhino "
"pubbantāparantaṃ ārabbha anekavihitāni adhimuttipadāni abhivadanti, sabbe te "
"imeheva dvāsaṭṭhiyā vatthūhi, etesaṃ vā aññatarena;"
msgstr ""
"Any ascetics and brahmins who theorize about the past or the future do so on "
"one or other of these sixty-two grounds. Outside of this there is none."

msgctxt "dn1:194.2"
msgid "natthi ito bahiddhā."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="170"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:195.1"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato pajānāti:"
msgstr "The Realized One understands this:"

msgctxt "dn1:195.2"
msgid ""
"‘ime diṭṭhiṭṭhānā evaṅgahitā evaṃparāmaṭṭhā evaṅgatikā bhavanti "
"evaṃabhisamparāyā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If you hold on to and attach to these grounds for views it leads to such "
"and such a destiny in the next life.’ "

msgctxt "dn1:195.3"
msgid ""
"Tañca tathāgato pajānāti, tato ca uttaritaraṃ pajānāti, tañca pajānanaṃ na "
"parāmasati, aparāmasato cassa paccattaññeva nibbuti viditā."
msgstr ""
"Yet since he does not misapprehend that understanding, he has realized "
"extinguishment within himself."

msgctxt "dn1:195.4"
msgid ""
"Vedanānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca "
"yathābhūtaṃ viditvā anupādāvimutto, bhikkhave, tathāgato."
msgstr ""
"Having truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, drawback and "
"escape from feelings, the Realized One is freed through not grasping."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="171"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:196.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho te, bhikkhave, dhammā gambhīrā duddasā duranubodhā santā paṇītā "
"atakkāvacarā nipuṇā paṇḍitavedanīyā, ye tathāgato sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā "
"pavedeti, yehi tathāgatassa yathābhuccaṃ vaṇṇaṃ sammā vadamānā vadeyyuṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are the principles—deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, "
"sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute—"
"which the Realized One makes known after realizing them with his own "
"insight. And those who genuinely praise the Realized One would rightly speak "
"of these things."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "dn1:197.1"
msgid "4. Attālokapaññattivatthu"
msgstr "The Grounds For Assertions About the Self and the Cosmos"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "dn1:198.1"
msgid "4.1. Paritassitavipphanditavāra"
msgstr "Anxiety and Evasiveness"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="172"></a><a class="pts" id="pts1.40"></a>
msgctxt "dn1:199.1"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bhikkhave, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā sassatavādā sassataṃ attānañca "
"lokañca paññapenti catūhi vatthūhi, tadapi tesaṃ bhavataṃ samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṃ "
"ajānataṃ apassataṃ vedayitaṃ taṇhāgatānaṃ paritassitavipphanditameva."
msgstr ""
"Now, these things are only the feeling of those who do not know or see, the "
"agitation and evasiveness of those under the sway of craving. Namely, when "
"those ascetics and brahmins assert that the self and the cosmos are eternal "
